Bug.WithStack:
package p;
class A{
    
    public String toString() {
        return super.toString();
    }

}

1. turn on the single method view
2. select toString in the outliner
3. select the word 'super' in that method
4. press alt+up (exactly 5 times)
5. the whole class is selected
4. press alt+up once more

package declaration is shown - expected to see the whole file content
the selection starts at the package declaration element and therefore it 
becomes the active element. Pressing alt downs behaves properly.


Post 2.0
As of now 'LATER' and 'REMIND' resolutions are no longer supported.
Please reopen this bug if it is still valid for you.

