source_code.code:
while (stepIndex < steps.length) {
	WizardStep step = steps[stepIndex];
	stepGroup.setCurrentStep(step);
	IWizard stepWizard = step.getWizard();
	setWizard(stepWizard);
	if (stepWizard.getPageCount() > 0)
		return;
	else
		performFinish();
}

Bug.WithStack:
Build 20020319

1) Follow the steps in bug 8961.

When the error occurs, hit ok.  The error dialog pops up again.  No matter what 
you do, it keeps popping up the dialog.  You have to kill eclipse to get out of 
it.  The guilty code is in:

org.eclipse.ui.internal.dialogs.MultiStepConfigureWizardPage$WizardStepContainer
.processCurrentStep() line: 353

while (stepIndex < steps.length) {
	WizardStep step = steps[stepIndex];
	stepGroup.setCurrentStep(step);
	IWizard stepWizard = step.getWizard();
	setWizard(stepWizard);
	if (stepWizard.getPageCount() > 0)
		return;
	else
		performFinish();
}

If performFinish fails, stepIndex does not get incremented, and the while loop 
continues forever.
Although this code is no longer used, this bug should be addressed since it's 
likely we will revisit capabilities post 2.0.


Defer until after release 2.0  Also, when the capability stuff is exposed 
again, it will probably not use the step wizard and thus this problem will go 
away.
As of now 'LATER' and 'REMIND' resolutions are no longer supported.
Please reopen this bug if it is still valid for you.

